WEBVTT

00:00:00.634 --> 00:00:03.146
So if I was to ask you

00:00:03.170 --> 00:00:04.560
what the connection between

00:00:04.584 --> 00:00:07.832
a bottle of Tide detergent and sweat was,

00:00:07.856 --> 00:00:09.496
you'd probably think
that's the easiest question

00:00:09.520 --> 00:00:12.276
that you're going to be asked
in Edinburgh all week.

00:00:12.300 --> 00:00:14.915
But if I was to say
that they're both examples

00:00:14.939 --> 00:00:18.144
of alternative or new forms of currency

00:00:18.168 --> 00:00:21.682
in a hyperconnected,
data-driven global economy,

00:00:21.706 --> 00:00:25.211
you'd probably think
I was a little bit bonkers.

00:00:25.235 --> 00:00:27.778
But trust me, I work in advertising.

00:00:27.802 --> 00:00:29.811
(Laughter)

00:00:29.835 --> 00:00:31.870
And I am going to tell you the answer,